{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17493157","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17493157"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:58:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:58:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1241"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1241","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1241"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.63,0.03,0.17,0.03,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1241"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109049"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1241","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1241"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1241"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91415"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"527"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"1769"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"5820"},{"type":"tags","id":"6523"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7305"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8543"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8676"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18471"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35590"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38080"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40681"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109049","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109049"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 81-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a two-week history of vague abdominal pain. Because of cognitive impairment he is a poor historian and no collateral information is available. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. He lives alone and is independent with activities of daily living.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears unwell. His pulse rate is 88/min, blood pressure 124/80\u00a0mmHg, respiratory rate 13/min, SpO\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E 97% on room air, and temperature 37.6\u00a0\u00b0C. Cardiorespiratory examination is unremarkable. He lies with his right hip flexed and experiences marked pain when asked to extend that leg. A CT scan is performed (Images 1 - 2).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely underlying cause of his current problem?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Appendicitis","Cholecystitis","Diverticulitis","Pancreatitis","Pyelonephritis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s inability to fully extend his right leg and the presence of a low-grade fever suggest a psoas abscess. This is confirmed via the CT scan, which shows a homogenous attenuated fluid-filled mass that is adjacent to and pressing on the psoas.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is most likely that the abscess has developed from an infected and inflamed adjacent structure. In this case given the location of the abscess, this likely developed secondary to an episode of \u003Cstrong\u003Eappendicitis\u003C/strong\u003E, which is the most frequent intra-abdominal source of right sided psoas abscess.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst all the listed conditions could present with abscess formation, the most realistic pathological process is appendicitis. When \u003Cstrong\u003Epyelonephritis\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with abscess formation, this usually develops around or near to the kidney. Likewise pancreatic abscess formation secondary to \u003Cstrong\u003Epancreatitis\u003C/strong\u003E tends to occur around the pancreas, and when severe, more typically involves the anterior pararenal space rather than the psoas sheath. Diverticular abscess formation from \u003Cstrong\u003Ediverticulitis\u003C/strong\u003E is relatively common and being an intraperitoneal structure, any abscess originating from the colon usually forms within the peritoneal cavity rather than within the psoas sheath. Abscess formation related to \u003Cstrong\u003Echolecystitis\u003C/strong\u003E is uncommon and when it does occur it is usually an intraperitoneal process.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case the abscess was drained percutaneously. A sample would have been taken at time of drainage for culture and sensitivities to confirm an enteric origin and tailor antimicrobial therapy. Follow up is important, as recurrence is possible and in the elderly this can portend morbidity and mortality.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Psoas abscess formation is uncommon and usually associated with fever, flank pain and muscle spasm."],"references":["Shields D, Robinson P, Crowley Tp. Iliopsoas abscess e A review and update on the literature .Int J Surg. 2012; 10:466-69. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22960467/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91415"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1241"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19888"},{"type":"media","id":"19889"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19888","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19888"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/92cb941d-703a-4bbc-8f01-67336e875206.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/92cb941d-703a-4bbc-8f01-67336e875206.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":522,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"19889","links":{"self"